@startuml
title Decision Tree: Choosing a Rendering Strategy

start

:Is the content user-specific?;

if (Yes) then (Yes)
  :Use **SSR** (Server-Side Rendering);
  note right
    Examples: Cart, auth-gated pages,
    real-time feeds
  end note
  stop
else (No)
  :Can I tolerate N seconds of staleness?;
  if (No) then (No)
    :Use **SSR**;
    note right: Must be always fresh
    stop
  else (Yes)
    :Does the content ever change?;
    if (Never changes) then (Never)
      :Use **SSG** (Static Generation);
      note right: Built once at deploy time
      stop
    else (Changes)
      :Use **ISR** (Incremental Static Regeneration);
      note right: revalidate: N seconds
      stop
    endif
  endif
endif

@enduml